{
  "texts": [
    "This imperative is to maximize the evidence (a.k.a.",
    "marginal likelihood) for generative (a.k.a., world) models of how observations are caused.",
    "This imperative can be expressed as minimizing an evidence bound called variational free energy (Winn and Bishop, 2005) that comprises complexity and accuracy (Ramstead et al., 2022):",
    "Free energy = model complexity -model accuracy.",
    "Accuracy corresponds to goodness of fit, while complexity scores the divergence between prior beliefs (before seeing outcomes) and posterior beliefs (afterwards)."
  ]
}